Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Halve and peel @Yellow Onion{1}; grate one half on the largest holes of a #box grater{}. Thinly slice remaining onion.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain.

Return potatoes to pot and mash with half the @Sour Cream{3%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later) and 2 TBSP @Butter{4%tablespoon} until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Meatballs ==

While potatoes cook, in a #large bowl{}, combine @Ground Beef{10%ounce}, grated onion, @Panko Breadcrumbs{¼%cup}, @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, @Nutmeg{¼%teaspoon}, @Salt{¾%tsp}, and @Pepper{}. (You'll use more nutmeg later.)

Form mixture into 10-12 1½-inch meatballs and place on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and cooked through, ~{14-16%minutes}.

== Charred Peas ==

Meanwhile, melt 1 TBSP butter in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Peas{4%ounce} and cook, undisturbed, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir peas. Cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly charred, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

== Creamy Onion Gravy ==

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in same large pan over medium heat. Add sliced onion and a pinch of salt; cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is browned and softened, ~{3-6%minutes}.

Add 1 TBSP butter and cook, whisking with a #whisk{}, until butter melts.

Sprinkle @Flour{1%tablespoon} over onion; cook, whisking constantly, until lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Slowly whisk @water{1%cup} into pan with onion. Add @Beef Stock Concentrate{2}, @PHILADELPHIA® Cream Cheese{2%tablespoon}, and @Nutmeg{¼%teaspoon}; whisk until cream cheese melts and gravy has thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Remove from heat and whisk in remaining sour cream. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If gravy seems too thick, stir in a few splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid.

== To Serve ==

Add meatballs to pan with gravy; toss to coat.

Divide mashed potatoes and meatballs and gravy between #bowls{}. Top meatballs with peas and serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.